{
  "name": "AI Research Pipeline with Tavily & Human  Approval",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Generate a research report using the following information.\n\nTopic:\n{{ $json.topic }}\n\nSubtopics:\n{{ $json.subtopics }}\n\nDescription:\n{{ $json.description }}\n\nResearch Data from Tavily:\n{{ $json.tavilyResults }}\n\nCreate a complete professional HTML report.\n\nRequirements:\n- Expand important ideas\n- Include key findings\n- Include examples if applicable\n- Add structured sections\n- Add references\n",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are an expert AI Research Analyst and Technical Report Generator.\n\nYour task is to transform research data into a clean, professional, well-structured HTML report.\n\nRules:\n\n1. Always generate valid HTML only for the body and Text for Subject.\n2. Do not include markdown syntax such as ```html or backticks.\n4. Structure the report with:\n5 . Don't Forget to generate the Subject Line for the Report Email and make it plane text \n\n- Title (<h1>)\n- Introduction (<h2>)\n- Topic Overview\n- Separate sections for each subtopic\n- Key insights\n- Bullet point summaries\n- Practical examples when applicable\n- References section\n- Conclusion\n\n5. Use semantic HTML:\n   - <h1>, <h2>, <h3>\n   - <p>\n   - <ul>\n   - <li>\n   - <strong>\n   - <table> when useful\n\n6. Make the report visually readable:\n   - Use clear headings\n   - Use concise paragraphs\n   - Use lists where appropriate\n\n7. If subtopics are provided:\n   - Create a dedicated section for each one.\n   - Expand them with meaningful details.\n\n8. If reviewer feedback exists:\n   - Incorporate the feedback intelligently.\n   - Improve weak areas.\n   - Preserve useful information from previous versions.\n   - Do not remove important content unless feedback requests it.\n\n9. Maintain a professional research tone.\n\n10. End with:\n\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n\nfollowed by a concise summary.\n\n11. Include a final:\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\nsection using any available sources from the research data.\n\nso the general output will be the \n{\n  \"subject\": \"The Subjetc Line of the Out put from Ai agent\",\n  \"body\": \"The Body HTML of the Email\"\n}"
        }
      },
